FT  25 MAR 94 / From beer - via tea and ice cream - to spirits
Making a giant: Buying Pedro Domecq Group for Pounds 739m turns
Allied-Lyons into the world's second largest spirits producer with 13 of
the top 100 brands
Killing a name: Lyons, famous to generations for ice cream, tea and
Corner Houses, is dropped and the company becomes Allied Domecq
Ending a dynasty: Founded 264 years ago, family-owned Pedro Domecq is
one of the oldest sherry companies in Jerez.
